{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-998fe92771b817d0", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# AISHELL-1: An Open-Source Mandarin Speech Corpus and A Speech Recognition Baseline\narXiv: 1709.05522\nAuthors: Hui Bu, Jiayu Du, Xingyu Na, Bengu Wu, Hao Zheng\nYear: 2017 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_dataset\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Release of AISHELL-1, the largest open-source Mandarin speech corpus suitable for speech recognition research.\n  2. Provision of a detailed corpus profile including recording procedures, speaker metadata, and multi-device capture setups.\n  3. Creation of normalized transcriptions and a Chinese lexicon covering commonly used words and characters.\n  4. Establishment of a Kaldi-based speech recognition baseline demonstrating promising audio and transcription quality.\n  5. Evaluation of the baseline models across high-fidelity, mobile, and cross-domain test sets to verify corpus robustness.\n\nTags: ASR, ASR/训练-监督", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "7484d82f-a85d-41b0-9df4-52973e966c03", "uuid": "3719d243-eb58-4791-bd7f-2e12a292c5ba", "timestamp": "2026-07-16T08:05:55.586Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# AISHELL-1: An Open-Source Mandarin Speech Corpus and A Speech Recognition Baseline\narXiv: 1709.05522\nAuthors: Hui Bu, Jiayu Du, Xingyu Na, Bengu Wu, Hao Zheng\nYear: 2017 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_dataset\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Release of AISHELL-1, the largest open-source Mandarin speech corpus suitable for speech recognition research.\n  2. Provision of a detailed corpus profile including recording procedures, speaker metadata, and multi-device capture setups.\n  3. Creation of normalized transcriptions and a Chinese lexicon covering commonly used words and characters.\n  4. Establishment of a Kaldi-based speech recognition baseline demonstrating promising audio and transcription quality.\n  5. Evaluation of the baseline models across high-fidelity, mobile, and cross-domain test sets to verify corpus robustness.\n\nTags: ASR, ASR/训练-监督", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-9c5df65619ee7ad4", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# StyleTTS 2: Towards Human-Level Text-to-Speech through Style Diffusion and Adversarial Training with Large Speech Language Models\narXiv: 2306.07691\nAuthors: Yinghao Aaron Li, Cong Han, Vinay S. Raghavan, Gavin Mischler, Nima Mesgarani\nYear: 2023 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Modeling speech styles as a latent random variable sampled via a diffusion model to generate diverse speech without requiring reference audio.\n  2. Employing large pre-trained speech language models as discriminators with a novel differentiable duration modeling approach for end-to-end adversarial training.\n  3. Introducing a non-parametric differentiable duration upsampler that enables stable gradient flow for end-to-end training with adversarial objectives.\n  4. Decoupling acoustic and prosodic style representations through separate style encoders to improve sample quality during joint training.\n  5. Achieving human-level text-to-speech synthesis that surpasses human recordings on the single-speaker LJSpeech dataset and matches them on the multispeaker VCTK dataset.\n  6. Demonstrating data-efficient zero-shot speaker adaptation that outperforms previous publicly available models using significantly less training data than large-scale pre-training methods.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Diffusion, TTS/控制-风格标签, TTS/功能-多说话人", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "7484d82f-a85d-41b0-9df4-52973e966c03", "uuid": "4c9fe3b5-ac5c-4e2c-9b4d-87c9f45bfc15", "timestamp": "2026-07-16T08:05:55.839Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# StyleTTS 2: Towards Human-Level Text-to-Speech through Style Diffusion and Adversarial Training with Large Speech Language Models\narXiv: 2306.07691\nAuthors: Yinghao Aaron Li, Cong Han, Vinay S. Raghavan, Gavin Mischler, Nima Mesgarani\nYear: 2023 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Modeling speech styles as a latent random variable sampled via a diffusion model to generate diverse speech without requiring reference audio.\n  2. Employing large pre-trained speech language models as discriminators with a novel differentiable duration modeling approach for end-to-end adversarial training.\n  3. Introducing a non-parametric differentiable duration upsampler that enables stable gradient flow for end-to-end training with adversarial objectives.\n  4. Decoupling acoustic and prosodic style representations through separate style encoders to improve sample quality during joint training.\n  5. Achieving human-level text-to-speech synthesis that surpasses human recordings on the single-speaker LJSpeech dataset and matches them on the multispeaker VCTK dataset.\n  6. Demonstrating data-efficient zero-shot speaker adaptation that outperforms previous publicly available models using significantly less training data than large-scale pre-training methods.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Diffusion, TTS/控制-风格标签, TTS/功能-多说话人", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
