{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Base directory for this skill: /inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/iHateTheWorld555.github.io/.claude-review/skills/free-search\n\n# Skill: free-search\n\nFree AI search engine — aggregate results from multiple sources in parallel.\n\n**Trigger**: user mentions free-search, search web, web search, 搜索, 搜一下, free search\n\n## How It Works\n\nRoutes queries to multiple OpenCLI adapters in parallel, merges and deduplicates results.\nFalls back gracefully — if one source fails, others still return results.\n\n## Usage\n\n```bash\n# Basic search\nfree-search \"your query\"\n\n# Limit results per source (default: 5)\nfree-search \"your query\" --limit 3\n\n# Search specific category\nfree-search \"your query\" --category general\nfree-search \"your query\" --category tech\nfree-search \"your query\" --category academic\nfree-search \"your query\" --category dev\nfree-search \"your query\" --category reference\nfree-search \"your query\" --category chinese\n\n# Search specific source\nfree-search \"your query\" --source hackernews\nfree-search \"your query\" --source arxiv\n\n# JSON output for piping to LLMs\nfree-search \"your query\" -f json\n\n# List available sources\nfree-search --list-sources\n```\n\n## Search Categories\n\n| Category | Sources (currently available) | Best for |\n|----------|---------|----------|\n| **general** | hackernews, wikipedia | General web search |\n| **tech** | hackernews, lobsters, lesswrong, producthunt, bilibili | Tech news & discussion |\n| **academic** | arxiv, dblp, openalex, openreview, pubmed | Papers & research |\n| **dev** | stackoverflow, npm, crates, mdn, dockerhub, devto | Code & packages |\n| **reference** | wikipedia, wikidata, dictionary, oeis | Facts & definitions |\n| **chinese** | bing, bilibili, xiaohongshu, zhihu | Chinese content |\n\n## Currently Available Sources (no browser needed)\n\nhackernews, stackoverflow, wikipedia, arxiv, dblp, openalex, openreview, pubmed, npm, crates, mdn, dictionary, wikidata, oeis, lobsters, lesswrong, producthunt, devto, dockerhub, substack, **bing** (direct API), **bilibili** (direct API), **xiaohongshu** (Playwright+cookies), **zhihu** (official API)\n\n## API Key Sources (keys.json in skill directory)\n\n- **zhihu**: requires `access_secret` from https://developer.zhihu.com — stored in `keys.json`\n\n## Browser-Required Sources (need OpenCLI Browser Bridge + external network)\n\nduckduckgo, brave, google, reddit, twitter, weibo, hupu, smzdm, 36kr, v2ex, linux-do, google-scholar, baidu-scholar, wanfang, cnki\n\n## Output Format\n\nEach result contains:\n- `source`: which adapter returned it\n- `title`: result title\n- `url`: link (if available)\n- `snippet`: short description/excerpt\n- `metadata`: source-specific fields (score, authors, etc.)\n\n## Notes\n\n- Speed: ~10s for parallel search across all available sources (default timeout per source)\n- Reliability: public API sources work without login; browser sources need browser bridge\n- Rate limits: arxiv may 429 on rapid successive queries; the script handles timeouts gracefully\n- Deduplication: results with same URL or title across sources are merged\n\n\nARGUMENTS: \"passive acoustic monitoring AIS alignment underwater acoustic dataset\" --category academic"}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "7484d82f-a85d-41b0-9df4-52973e966c03", "uuid": "af269a0e-1925-48c2-bb86-d0c715c972a6", "timestamp": "2026-07-16T08:05:55.849Z", "isSynthetic": true}
